The park has undergone various name changes over the years. It began as the Sieur de Monts National Park in 1916, when President Woodrow Wilson granted the park federal status.&nbsp; It was then renamed Lafayette National Park in 1919.&nbsp; It did not take the name of Acadia National Park until 1929. The name &quot;Acadia&quot; is a tribute to the former French colony of Acadia, which once included what is now the state of Maine.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"ju-examples\">(</span>p. 17)</span></p></td></tr></tbody></table><p>&nbsp;</p>","rightText":null},{"settings":{"showAudio":1,"showNext":1,"showHeader":0,"hideRightPanel":1,"delayStep":0,"delayRight":0,"showRuler":0,"showRFB":1},"leftText":"<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\" class=\"ju-powertip\" style=\"width:90%;\"><thead><tr><th scope=\"col\">ASK YOURSELF:&nbsp;
